+## Environment Variables
+
+| Variable | Default | Description |
+|----------|---------|-------------|
+| `ZEND_STATE_DIR` | `./state` | Where to store principal and pairing data |
+| `ZEND_BIND_HOST` | `127.0.0.1` | Interface to bind (LAN: your LAN IP) |
+| `ZEND_BIND_PORT` | `8080` | Port to listen on |
+| `ZEND_DAEMON_URL` | `http://127.0.0.1:8080` | CLI daemon endpoint |
+
+## Key Concepts
+
+**PrincipalId** — A stable UUID identity shared by gateway pairing and the event spine.
+The same ID owns miner control and future inbox access.
+
+**Capability** — Permission scope. Phase one has two: `observe` (read status) and `control`
+(change modes). A paired observer cannot control the miner.
+
+**Event Spine** — An append-only encrypted journal. Pairing approvals, control receipts,
+alerts, and Hermes summaries all flow through here. The inbox is a derived view.
+
+**MinerSnapshot** — Cached miner status with a freshness timestamp. The client can tell
+"live" from "stale".
